1
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:11,810
[ENDEAVOR growls]

2
00:00:11,890 --> 00:00:15,100
[yells]

3
00:00:23,060 --> 00:00:26,650
What happened to...
to my strength?

4
00:00:31,490 --> 00:00:33,740
[MIRIO]
The sedative worked!

5
00:00:33,830 --> 00:00:37,250
[BEST JEANIST] I do not know
who accomplished this...

6
00:00:37,330 --> 00:00:40,920
...but our hopes
have been repaired.

7
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,340
The fact that
this drug kicked in

8
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:46,170
at the 11th hour
isn't a coincidence.

9
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:49,250
We've been chipping away at
this villain little by little,

10
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:52,840
using whatever meager power
we were able to cobble together.

11
00:00:52,930 --> 00:00:57,520
Sacrificing ourselves to break
his spirit and slow him down.

12
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,230
We held him off as best we could

13
00:00:59,310 --> 00:01:02,610
until the drug had
time to take effect.

14
00:01:02,690 --> 00:01:05,150
If I've learned one thing
through my Quirk,

15
00:01:05,230 --> 00:01:07,860
it's that, though a
single fiber is weak,

16
00:01:07,940 --> 00:01:12,360
it can be braided with others
to form a mighty rope.

17
00:01:12,450 --> 00:01:15,370
[BEST JEANIST coughs]
Had even one thread broken,

18
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:16,990
we would have failed.

19
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:20,540
It's only together that we've
woven a tapestry of faith.

20
00:02:56,930 --> 00:02:58,560
[MR. COMPRESS grunting]

21
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,680
[MR. COMPRESS]
What a shameful predicament.

22
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,680
All I can do is grope
my own posterior.

23
00:03:03,770 --> 00:03:05,730
You're no better, Shigaraki.

24
00:03:05,810 --> 00:03:08,060
Remember why you
summoned us here?

25
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:11,570
We were supposed to gather
together and create a spectacle.

26
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:13,990
What'd you have to go
and get beaten up for?

27
00:03:14,070 --> 00:03:15,820
Now we're trapped!

28
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:19,070
There's so much left
in this world to destroy.

29
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,040
[MR. COMPRESS]
It's just as Spinner said.

30
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:23,660
We haven't done anything yet.

31
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:25,420
Not Dabi.

32
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,000
Nor Toga.

33
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,870
Nor I.

34
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:31,710
None of us have
achieved our dreams!

35
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:33,300
[BEST JEANIST]
Blackout Bind!

36
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:36,340
[MR. COMPRESS grunts]
This cannot be

37
00:03:36,420 --> 00:03:38,550
where our performance ends!

38
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:45,850
[MR. COMPRESS]
The other League members

39
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:48,350
never asked about my past.

40
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:50,570
We were a group
of twisted players,

41
00:03:50,650 --> 00:03:53,110
only concerned about ourselves.

42
00:03:55,820 --> 00:03:57,110
[MR. COMPRESS]
Even so.

43
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,660
With them...

44
00:03:58,740 --> 00:04:01,280
[CRC MEMBER 126A] Why have you
entered our compound?

45
00:04:01,370 --> 00:04:02,830
[CRC MEMBER 126B]
Do you know who we are?

46
00:04:02,910 --> 00:04:04,450
Do you seek to join us?

47
00:04:04,540 --> 00:04:06,880
[SPINNER]
The Creature Rejection Clan.

48
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,170
AKA the CRC.

49
00:04:09,250 --> 00:04:11,750
You bastards spew
outdated ideas.

50
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:14,630
Discriminating against
heteromorphs like me.

51
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,760
You're bigots.

52
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,010
[CRC MEMBER 126C]
They brought a pet.

53
00:04:19,090 --> 00:04:20,300
[CRC MEMBER 126AA]
Repulsive.

54
00:04:20,390 --> 00:04:21,220
[CRC MEMBER 126A]
Hold on.

55
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,010
This is the League of Villains!

56
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,480
[MR. COMPRESS] We're currently
a tad short on funds.

57
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:28,100
So we're in the market
for things to sell.

58
00:04:28,180 --> 00:04:29,220
Are these rare?

59
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:30,150
[CRC MEMBER 126D]
Don't touch!

60
00:04:30,230 --> 00:04:31,860
[MR. COMPRESS]
I know, I know.

61
00:04:31,940 --> 00:04:34,360
Burglary isn't the most
fashionable crime.

62
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,780
I wish we didn't have
to resort to it.

63
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:38,610
[CRC MEMBER 126BB]
This is sacred ground!

64
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,240
[CRC MEMBER 126E]
Filthy criminals!

65
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,910
[CRC MEMBER 126A]
You'll pay for your impudence!

66
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:45,910
[SHIGARAKI] We'll leave
when we have what we want.

67
00:04:45,990 --> 00:04:48,490
You'd be smart to
stay out of our way.

68
00:04:50,830 --> 00:04:52,170
[CRC MEMBER 126B]
Kill them!

69
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:59,550
[TWICE] Thought these culty
types were supposed to be rich!

70
00:04:59,630 --> 00:05:01,720
[TOGA]
Dumb skull faces got nothin'!

71
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,550
[TWICE]
This crap looks valuable!

72
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:05,180
Nothing special.

73
00:05:05,260 --> 00:05:08,220
Ah! They broke it.

74
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:10,230
[MR. COMPRESS]
My prosthetic arm is creaky.

75
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:12,480
Let's have Giran
get us new gear.

76
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:13,810
[TWICE]
Great idea!

77
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:17,320
We have no money
to pay him with.

78
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,860
[SPINNER]
Boss.

79
00:05:18,940 --> 00:05:20,320
This is no way to live.

80
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:22,240
How long can we keep this up?

81
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:25,660
As long as it takes.
Until we're finished.

82
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:27,580
[MR. COMPRESS] If we'd teamed
up with the Hassaikai,

83
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:30,250
we'd probably be eating
the finest sushi right now.

84
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:31,330
[SHIGARAKI]
Don't be an idiot.

85
00:05:31,410 --> 00:05:33,870
[MR. COMPRESS laughs]
What a world.

86
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,500
We spread fear
across the country,

87
00:05:35,590 --> 00:05:38,180
and now we're reduced
to a band of paupers.

88
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:41,550
I feel pity for every lunatic
who looked up to us.

89
00:05:41,630 --> 00:05:43,380
[TWICE]
Nothing here of any interest.

90
00:05:43,470 --> 00:05:46,520
Huh? Uh, speak for yourself.
I'm keepin' this.

91
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,060
[TWICE]
Oh, it's lovely!

92
00:05:48,140 --> 00:05:51,390
For an old lady. Toss it.

93
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,650
Typical.

94
00:05:52,730 --> 00:05:55,780
The whole gang's
just sittin' around.

95
00:05:55,860 --> 00:05:57,740
Am I the only one
who's actually working

96
00:05:57,820 --> 00:05:59,110
to find us some more members?

97
00:05:59,190 --> 00:06:00,570
[TWICE]
All you're doin' is goin' around

98
00:06:00,650 --> 00:06:02,240
burning people to death!

99
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,740
Have you ever brought
back a single person?

100
00:06:04,820 --> 00:06:06,910
[DABI]
Not my fault nobody's worthy.

101
00:06:06,990 --> 00:06:09,990
The streets are full of walking
trash with no ambition.

102
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,120
Maybe you're just a bad
judge of character.

103
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:15,010
[DABI]
Please. Like you're one to talk.

104
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:19,290
So. What exactly's our
top priority these days?

105
00:06:21,210 --> 00:06:24,010
I joined the League because
I was inspired by Stain.

106
00:06:24,090 --> 00:06:25,300
What?

107
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:27,730
I'm from a backwater town
in the countryside.

108
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:30,890
Everyone there believed
old-fashioned ideas.

109
00:06:30,970 --> 00:06:34,890
And shunned me
because of how I look.

110
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:38,230
I can't describe
how hollow I felt.

111
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:40,810
Then, while watching
the news one night,

112
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:43,820
I witnessed Stain's
final moments.

113
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:48,240
[SPINNER] He was trying to
change our antiquated society.

114
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,820
By himself.

115
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:52,370
That was the first time I
realized how suffocating

116
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:54,830
the culture around me was.

117
00:06:54,910 --> 00:06:57,830
I couldn't sit back
and do nothing.

118
00:06:57,920 --> 00:07:00,760
And now I'm here!

119
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:01,920
Wow. Cool.

120
00:07:02,010 --> 00:07:04,010
So you're basically
an empty cosplayer.

121
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:07,260
[SPINNER] That's right!
I'm still completely empty.

122
00:07:07,340 --> 00:07:08,920
Which is why...

123
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:11,680
...I don't understand
why we're wasting time!

124
00:07:11,770 --> 00:07:14,650
I thought we were supposed
to break the world here.

125
00:07:14,730 --> 00:07:16,650
Answer me, Shigaraki!

126
00:07:16,730 --> 00:07:20,690
What the hell is our goal?
What're we doing?

127
00:07:20,770 --> 00:07:22,400
[MR. COMPRESS]
Until six months ago,

128
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:24,940
we were so strapped for cash,
we had to worry about

129
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:27,320
where our next meal
would come from.

130
00:07:27,410 --> 00:07:30,370
We also lacked
a unified vision.

131
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:33,450
And yet... How do I explain it?

132
00:07:33,540 --> 00:07:34,960
Simply put...

133
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:38,460
[MR. COMPRESS]
...I loved being in

134
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:40,710
the League of Villains, Spinner.

135
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:45,680
What're you talking about?

136
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:48,510
[MR. COMPRESS]
Our boss is the key.

137
00:07:48,590 --> 00:07:52,800
I'll buy you time
to wake him up.

138
00:07:52,890 --> 00:07:54,850
Use it well.

139
00:07:54,930 --> 00:08:00,600
Every good show
requires teamwork.

140
00:08:00,690 --> 00:08:03,530
This is my duty to my bloodline.

141
00:08:03,610 --> 00:08:05,740
The reason I'm here!

142
00:08:05,820 --> 00:08:06,990
[MR. COMPRESS groans]

143
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,530
[BEST JEANIST gasps]

144
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:10,950
[MR. COMPRESS] Gouging my own
flesh loosened the bindings.

145
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:14,530
My arm is free. And so are you!

146
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,450
[TENYA]
The League!

147
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:19,130
[MIRIO] They've escaped
their restraints!

148
00:08:19,210 --> 00:08:20,590
[MR. COMPRESS]
Don't think you're the only ones

149
00:08:20,670 --> 00:08:23,050
risking your lives for a cause!

150
00:08:23,130 --> 00:08:25,880
Now. Keep your eyes peeled.

151
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:29,670
This will be the performance
of a lifetime!

152
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,430
[BEST JEANIST] I can't
believe he'd use his Quirk

153
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:33,140
to carve up his own body.

154
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:34,930
What fortitude!

155
00:08:35,020 --> 00:08:37,940
Still. That wound looks fatal!

156
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:39,440
You will not escape!

157
00:08:40,690 --> 00:08:41,650
[MR. COMPRESS]
Clever!

158
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,650
He's imprisoning me
with my clothes.

159
00:08:43,730 --> 00:08:47,820
But I'm perfectly positioned for
a little sleight of hand magic.

160
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:50,490
Goodbye, costume!

161
00:08:50,570 --> 00:08:52,530
[BEST JEANIST]
He got away.

162
00:08:52,620 --> 00:08:54,620
[CHIKAZOKU]
H-Hey. Over here!

163
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:55,700
I can't move!

164
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:57,500
Don't leave me!

165
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:00,420
[MR. COMPRESS]
I'm a master

166
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:04,250
when it comes to trickery
and deft escapes.

167
00:09:04,340 --> 00:09:09,930
Those talents are all I need
to save us from abysmal defeat.

168
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:11,220
[MR. COMPRESS'S DAD]
Atsuhiro.

169
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:19,360
[MR. COMPRESS]
Oji Harima: the peerless thief.

170
00:09:19,430 --> 00:09:22,430
A criminal from days long past.

171
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:23,900
When the current system

172
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:27,070
was starting to take shape,
he stole from false heroes

173
00:09:27,150 --> 00:09:29,530
who cared only about
lining their pockets.

174
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:32,110
[MR. COMPRESS] As he spread
his loot among the needy,

175
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:35,160
he preached social reform.

176
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,530
[MR. COMPRESS'S DAD]
My son.

177
00:09:36,620 --> 00:09:39,660
The spirit of justice flows
through our family line.

178
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:42,460
It's our duty to
expose unfairness.

179
00:09:44,130 --> 00:09:45,010
[TODOROKI]
Flashfire...

180
00:09:45,090 --> 00:09:46,380
...Fist!

181
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:48,210
Jet Kindling!

182
00:09:48,300 --> 00:09:49,970
No. Jetburn!

183
00:09:53,220 --> 00:09:54,970
[TODOROKI groans]

184
00:09:55,050 --> 00:09:59,300
I'm sorry, Shoto.
We'll dance again later.

185
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:02,230
Enji Todoroki hasn't
suffered enough to break,

186
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:05,520
and there's no point in
continuing if he's knocked out.

187
00:10:05,610 --> 00:10:08,030
Too bad, little masterpiece!

188
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:09,610
[MR. COMPRESS]
Dabi! Quick!

189
00:10:12,990 --> 00:10:14,740
[MR. COMPRESS]
It was a good run, Harima.

190
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:17,360
Though I didn't cause
the reform I wanted.

191
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:19,080
I know who will.

192
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,290
Tomura Shigaraki of the PLF

193
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:25,170
and the League of Villains will
change the world in my stead!

194
00:10:27,170 --> 00:10:30,380
[MR. COMPRESS] I'm Oji Harima's
great-great grandson.

195
00:10:30,460 --> 00:10:33,340
The blood of the bandit king
pumps through my veins.

196
00:10:33,430 --> 00:10:35,220
You barely noticed me, right?

197
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:38,140
That was part
of my grand deception!

198
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:42,100
My role was saved
for when it really mattered.

199
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:47,770
One must always keep
an ace up their sleeve.

200
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:49,650
I won't let you get away
with anything else!

201
00:10:49,730 --> 00:10:51,520
At last, center stage!

202
00:10:53,490 --> 00:10:57,620
[MR. COMPRESS] It's time for
Mr. Compress's spectacular,

203
00:10:57,700 --> 00:11:02,000
once in a lifetime escape act!

204
00:11:17,470 --> 00:11:18,220
[HERO 126A groans]

205
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,760
[yells]

206
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:22,060
[BURNIN yells]

207
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:27,060
[MASTER DRILLER]
I've got this one!

208
00:11:30,860 --> 00:11:32,570
No! Master Driller!

209
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:36,490
[MASTER DRILLER yells]

210
00:11:40,740 --> 00:11:44,450
Monster. You'll pay!

211
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:49,830
[FIRST WIELDER]
Wake up. You can't sleep now.

212
00:11:49,920 --> 00:11:51,880
Arise, Ninth Wielder.

213
00:11:59,090 --> 00:12:01,340
[IZUKU]
Was I KOed?

214
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:04,970
[IZUKU]
Dabi's blast knocked me back.

215
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:08,230
Then Endeavor...

216
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:09,730
Where's Todoroki?

217
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:12,070
[IZUKU]
Thank goodness.

218
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,780
I'm glad he--

219
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:15,780
There it is again!

220
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:18,450
I've felt this a few times
since the fight started.

221
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:22,080
A sharp, stabbing pain
in my head.

222
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:24,830
Wait a sec, this sounds like

223
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:27,000
something from
All Might's notes.

224
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,120
It's the Fourth User's Quirk.

225
00:12:29,210 --> 00:12:30,710
Danger Sense.

226
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:35,010
[IZUKU] I haven't started
training for this power yet.

227
00:12:35,090 --> 00:12:39,390
It's killing my head.
This isn't good.

228
00:12:39,470 --> 00:12:43,060
I have no control,
like when Blackwhip manifested.

229
00:12:45,770 --> 00:12:48,020
[IZUKU]
Can't black out!

230
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:49,980
[MR. COMPRESS]
At last, center stage!

231
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:53,860
Time for Mr. Compress's
spectacular,

232
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:56,530
once in a lifetime escape act!

233
00:12:57,650 --> 00:12:59,190
[MR. COMPRESS]
Admission is free!

234
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,280
Relax and enjoy the perfor--

235
00:13:03,910 --> 00:13:05,500
[MR. COMPRESS]
Don't banish me to the wings

236
00:13:05,580 --> 00:13:08,210
before the final curtain falls!

237
00:13:09,370 --> 00:13:10,830
[MR. COMPRESS]
On our way here,

238
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:13,380
I saw a horde of Nomu.

239
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:15,800
They only move on
Shigaraki's orders,

240
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:19,300
so he must've called them
sometime after he woke up.

241
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:21,420
Destroy it all.

242
00:13:21,510 --> 00:13:23,600
Machia.

243
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:25,680
[MR. COMPRESS] The boss spoke,
but from the look

244
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:28,930
and sound of it, he wasn't
completely awake.

245
00:13:29,020 --> 00:13:31,400
He must regain consciousness.

246
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,020
Then the League can
escape on the backs

247
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:36,100
of a bio-engineered chorus!

248
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:38,480
I bought them time.

249
00:13:38,570 --> 00:13:42,240
After all. I'm not
the lead in this play.

250
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:44,110
Just a diversion.

251
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:47,040
The rest is up
to luck and my crew.

252
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:50,920
I even managed to tuck
Dabi and Longhair away.

253
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,960
Don't let me down, Spinner.

254
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:55,670
You're the most devoted of us.

255
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:58,380
I'm just a
supporting character.

256
00:13:58,460 --> 00:14:02,380
You two are the real
stars of the show.

257
00:14:02,470 --> 00:14:06,020
[SPINNER] Now's our chance!
Dammit, wake up, Shigaraki!

258
00:14:08,810 --> 00:14:12,770
[SHIGARAKI] When I put
them on, it's so strange.

259
00:14:12,850 --> 00:14:14,230
Though it still
makes me feel sick

260
00:14:14,310 --> 00:14:18,230
to my stomach, wearing them
washes calmness over me.

261
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:20,200
Don't you think that's bizarre?

262
00:14:21,990 --> 00:14:24,200
[SPINNER] I'm not sure
this'll work, but...

263
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:27,200
I saw something stashed
in your melted suit.

264
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:30,330
Charred and crushed, but whole.

265
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:32,830
You need to remember
who you are.

266
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,870
[SHIGARAKI]
There's a heaviness in my heart,

267
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,550
like a lump of lead.

268
00:14:39,630 --> 00:14:43,260
Never moving, fueling
the rage that propels me

269
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:45,430
but never brings relief!

270
00:14:50,180 --> 00:14:51,220
[MIRIO gasps]

271
00:14:55,310 --> 00:14:56,900
[MIRIO yells]

272
00:14:56,980 --> 00:14:58,190
[BEST JEANIST]
What's this?

273
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:02,270
[TODOROKI grunts]

274
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:13,620
[IZUKU]
My head again. Don't tell me.

275
00:15:13,710 --> 00:15:15,630
Please, no!

276
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:22,250
[ALL FOR ONE] I must say, Tomura
has some admirable friends.

277
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:23,880
[SPINNER]
His voice.

278
00:15:23,970 --> 00:15:26,140
[ALL FOR ONE]
Power is drawn from the heart.

279
00:15:26,220 --> 00:15:29,180
The more he embraces
the pain and hatred born from

280
00:15:29,260 --> 00:15:35,560
his past trauma, the stronger my
will becomes within this body.

281
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,480
[SHIGARAKI]
I don't know why.

282
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:41,110
But there are so many bad
feelings inside of me.

283
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:45,190
No matter what I try,
they won't go away.

284
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:48,410
Then don't hold back.

285
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:50,160
Long live the king.

286
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,990
Tomura.

287
00:15:53,370 --> 00:15:54,700
They stopped?

288
00:15:58,580 --> 00:15:59,620
[HERO 126D]
This is our chance.

289
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:01,340
We'll take them out!

290
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:04,640
[HERO 126D]
A retreat?

291
00:16:04,710 --> 00:16:06,210
[BURNIN]
Same as before.

292
00:16:06,300 --> 00:16:08,140
They're heading for Shigaraki.

293
00:16:09,590 --> 00:16:13,510
[ALL FOR ONE] This is why the
Radio Waves Quirk is so crucial.

294
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:16,270
It can be used to send
long-distance signals

295
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:17,810
to the Nomu.

296
00:16:17,890 --> 00:16:22,100
Though it's difficult for Tomura
since he's a mere hatchling.

297
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:24,940
[TENYA]
What?

298
00:16:26,440 --> 00:16:27,570
[BEST JEANIST]
You're mine!

299
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:35,330
[BEST JEANIST]
Fight until the end!

300
00:16:35,410 --> 00:16:37,040
Do not give up!

301
00:16:38,870 --> 00:16:41,540
[SPINNER] Boss. How do you
want to attack them?

302
00:16:41,630 --> 00:16:43,130
[ALL FOR ONE]
We're withdrawing.

303
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,630
Wait, you wanna run?

304
00:16:44,710 --> 00:16:47,590
We can't do that!
Compress is hurt bad!

305
00:16:47,670 --> 00:16:50,010
And Machia's not going anywhere.

306
00:16:50,090 --> 00:16:53,090
Toga's supposed to be
heading this way, too!

307
00:16:53,180 --> 00:16:56,310
We're experts at doing
whatever we want.

308
00:16:56,390 --> 00:17:00,810
But... make sure that
you come back to us.

309
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:03,110
You're going to
abandon your comrades?

310
00:17:03,190 --> 00:17:04,940
[ALL FOR ONE]
Hold your tongue, Iguchi.

311
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:07,280
Did you say "Iguchi?"

312
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,700
Hold on. Who are you?

313
00:17:09,780 --> 00:17:12,280
[ALL FOR ONE]
Tomura already lost this fight.

314
00:17:12,370 --> 00:17:15,420
To One For All and Endeavor.

315
00:17:15,490 --> 00:17:17,740
He awoke before
his body modifications

316
00:17:17,830 --> 00:17:20,580
could be completed.
Unfortunately, this meant

317
00:17:20,670 --> 00:17:22,840
his regeneration
abilities were lacking

318
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:26,550
and no match for
the assembled heroes.

319
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:29,090
That's why I came
to lend my aid.

320
00:17:29,170 --> 00:17:32,880
The poor boy's body
is in dire need of rest.

321
00:17:32,970 --> 00:17:35,010
[SPINNER] I don't know
what you're going on about.

322
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:37,810
But you can't run away and
leave your teammates behind!

323
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,310
[ALL FOR ONE]
Yes. I can.

324
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:40,600
[SPINNER gasps]

325
00:17:40,690 --> 00:17:42,570
[ALL FOR ONE]
It's only fair that Tomura pays

326
00:17:42,650 --> 00:17:44,780
for his failures.

327
00:17:44,860 --> 00:17:48,780
Remember, this is
all for my sake.

328
00:17:48,860 --> 00:17:50,650
[BEST JEANIST] The League
is gathering in the same spot

329
00:17:50,740 --> 00:17:53,990
the Nomu are headed.
Dabi's probably there, too.

330
00:17:54,070 --> 00:17:55,860
Do not let them escape!

331
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:57,830
Output level 100.

332
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,830
Spiraling flood. Nejire Flood!

333
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:04,420
[TENYA]
Recipro Turbo!

334
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,790
I'll finish this in a flash,

335
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:10,130
then get Midoriya and
Bakugo to the hospital!

336
00:18:10,220 --> 00:18:14,600
After all, I became
a hero to save people!

337
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,350
[MIRIO]
You won't escape!

338
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,770
[ALL FOR ONE]
The Permeation Quirk, huh?

339
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:28,900
[ALL FOR ONE] I have no patience
for attacks I can't predict.

340
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:30,940
Shigaraki!

341
00:18:32,490 --> 00:18:34,870
[ALL FOR ONE]
Still, they swarm.

342
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,740
[TODOROKI, TENYA groan]

343
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:50,130
[ALL FOR ONE]
Now. Time to go.

344
00:18:50,210 --> 00:18:54,210
[IZUKU]
Move. Get up.

345
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:56,010
You can do this!

346
00:18:57,140 --> 00:19:00,640
[SHIGARAKI]
Learn your place, Master.

347
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,600
[IZUKU]
C'mon, Deku!

348
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:05,180
You can't just lie here!

349
00:19:05,270 --> 00:19:10,440
I'm in charge. This is my will.
The dream I chase is mine.

350
00:19:10,530 --> 00:19:13,990
[IZUKU]
Stand and fight these villains!

351
00:19:22,660 --> 00:19:27,210
[ALL FOR ONE]
Hm? You haven't given up yet?

352
00:19:27,290 --> 00:19:31,130
I'd say this child's tenacity
is comparable to All Might's.

353
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:41,640
[ALL FOR ONE]
The useless Izuku Midoriya.

354
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:44,680
Let's meet again when
this body's complete.

355
00:19:44,770 --> 00:19:48,980
You better keep your
mouth shut, All For One!

356
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:50,730
[ALL FOR ONE]
I'll see you soon.

357
00:19:54,990 --> 00:19:57,490
[IZUKU]
Shigaraki...

358
00:19:59,490 --> 00:20:02,950
[IZUKU]
You killed so many.

359
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:05,880
Everybody is in pain.

360
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,800
There's no way
I can forgive you.

361
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:11,510
Never.

362
00:20:11,590 --> 00:20:14,470
But...

363
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:17,800
Back there, when you
were being overtaken

364
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:20,550
by All For One.

365
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:25,440
I saw it. So clearly.

366
00:20:25,520 --> 00:20:31,480
You looked like
you wanted to be saved!

367
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:36,570
♪

368
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:29,820
[IZUKU]
Here's the preview.

369
00:23:29,910 --> 00:23:32,460
We battled fiercely,
but in the end,

370
00:23:32,540 --> 00:23:34,830
Shigaraki managed to escape.

371
00:23:34,910 --> 00:23:37,790
Many pros gave their lives,
and countless homes

372
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:41,180
and city blocks were destroyed
as a result of the fighting.

373
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:44,340
The country has lost
their faith in heroes.

374
00:23:44,420 --> 00:23:47,420
Is there still a future
where everyone can smile?

375
00:23:47,510 --> 00:23:50,140
Next time, "Hellish Hell."

376
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:53,890
This disaster will leave us all
with deep, painful scars.

377
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:56,230
Go beyond! Plus Ultra!

